         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Melbourne 20/2/72. ¶  ¶ I owe you my best thanks, dear and learned Sir, not only for your kindness of forwarding to me the samples of Demidium &amp; of ¶  ¶ Ricinacarpus ¶ Ricinocarpos? ¶  ¶ major, but al...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">72.02.20</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Alphonse de Candolle</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Bibliothèque des Conservatoire et Jardin botaniques, Geneva.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne 20/2/72.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I owe you my best thanks, dear and learned Sir, not only for your kindness of forwarding to me the samples of Demidium &amp; of<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">Ricinacarpus</seg>
               <seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">Ricinocarpos?</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>major, but also for mentioning my name specially in the last preface of your &amp; your great fathers universal work<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>A. P. de Candolle (1823-1873).<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>In<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Alphonse de Candolle's<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>'Historia, numeri, conclusio' in<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>the final volume of the work,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Vol.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>17, pp. 304-5,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>he wrote<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>'Inter omnes memorare juvat, propter dona speciminum preliosissima et numerosissima: peregrinatores vel botanicos …[Among all, it is useful to mention because of the gifts of the most valuable and numerous specimens:<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>travellers<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>or botanists…]. M is one of thirty-six in the list that follows.</p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <seg rend="rynqvb" style="color: #C00000; ">Check translation please. This is very rough</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and sending me an authographic inscription for the last volume, the value of which for<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">such</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>a work cannot too highly be esteemed.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>'Authorgraphic inscription' not identified.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Next to Linnés spec. plantarum<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn3" n="4">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Linnaeus (1753).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>the prodromus must always remain the greatest achievement of phytography; and as the material now will become scattered among so many future workers, no work can ever be produced, that can rank equal in importance with the prodromus.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have examined Demidium &amp; sent notes on it for the current 65th number of the Fragmenta to print.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn4" n="5">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>B74.03.01, pp. 145-6.</p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; margin-left: 0in; text-indent: 0in; color: #C00000; "
                        xml:lang="en">Letter is thanking<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>de<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>C for specimens requested in 73-07-00, so can't be 1872.</p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; margin-left: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #C00000; ">"Current" would be more compatible with a date of 187</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #C00000; ">4</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #C00000; ">, c.f. 73-05-20a</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #C00000; ">,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #C00000; ">noting that nothing of</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #C00000; ">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>vol 1</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #C00000; ">7</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #C00000; ">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>of<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont"
                             style="font-style: italic; color: #C00000; ">Prodromus,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #C00000; ">had yet arrived,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #C00000; ">but he has obviously seen it</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #C00000; ">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>when he wrote this</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #C00000; ">, with his name there among the Hookers, RBr, Martius, Cunningham, Philippi and so on.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                     </p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; margin-left: 0in; text-indent: 0in; color: #C00000; "
                        xml:lang="en">This vol was issued 16 October 1873, TL2, so it woud have had to be late 1873. Assuming the day and moth os correct, it has to be 1874.</p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; margin-left: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #C00000; ">I suspect that Vol 17 has the "</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #C00000; ">authographic inscription"</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #C00000; ">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>:<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #C00000; ">check library?</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #C00000; ">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>With<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #C00000; ">a lot of<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #C00000; ">luck, it<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #C00000; ">might</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #C00000; ">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>have a date of inscription.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                     </p>
                     <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Some of the flowers have a few<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">setae of a pappus</hi>
               </seg>, and it differs also in not having the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>recurved<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>involucre from Stuartina. I have now also described the anthers.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I shall not fail to send you from time to time contributions to your Herbarium, which must for all times remain one of the most important for consultation. I suppose your London adress is as in former years at Trübners.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">With profound regard your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Demidium</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">Ricinacarpus</seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>major</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Stuartina</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
         </div>
      </body>
